<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>7.3 Liter Diesel Engine Service (1991) - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS AND RINGS - CONNECTING RODS, PISTONS AND
        RINGS (Reconditioning) - Reassembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="5">
        <title>Reassembly</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate piston pin with clean engine oil. Align rod bore and piston bore and insert piston
                pin. Push piston pin with thumb and install retainer snap rings, using suitable pliers. Make sure
                retainers seat fully with tension in the grooves. See
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350539">5.39</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4350537" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11209" filename="../figcg1/cg11209.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.37 Checking Connecting Rod Bearing Clearance</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4350538" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11231" filename="../figcg1/cg11231.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.38 Checking Connecting Rod End Clearance</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4350539" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12356" filename="../figcg1/cg12356.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.39 Piston Pin Installation</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble the rings on the pistons to which they were fitted by using a piston ring expander
                tool,
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350540">5.40</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>This type of tool is recommended to avoid over-expanding and also to expand the ring to a true
                        circle to avoid distortion.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install rings with identification markings on ring facing up. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figures
                        <hotlnk document="e435_89.xml" xrefid="ef4350505">5.5</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    and
                    <emph type="bold">
                        <hotlnk document="e435_89.xml" xrefid="ef4350506">5.6</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Stagger the ring gaps 120&#176; apart.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install bearing shell inserts chosen during bearing fitting procedure. Bearing locator tangs
                (
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4350541">5.41</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                ) aid in correct insert installation.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Follow installation procedure for connecting rod and piston assembly as described earlier in
                this section.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>BE SURE TO USE THE ALUMINUM CONNECTING ROD GUIDE PROTECTOR CAPS ZTSE4153 TO PROTECT THE
                        CRANKSHAFT JOURNALS.
                    </para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Recheck connecting rod end play (see
                <hotlnk document="e435_HL4350501.xml" xrefid="hl4350501">"SPECIFICATIONS"</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reinstall all other components removed. See unit section for detailed reassembly
                procedures.
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4350540" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12357" filename="../figcg1/cg12357.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.40 Installing Piston Ring Using Piston Ring Expander Tool</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4350541" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg10567" filename="../figcg1/cg10567.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5.41 Bearing Shell Installation</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
